script supports a new type, module.<p><pre><code>    <script type=&quot;module&quot;>
        // loads the &#x27;q&#x27; export from &#x27;mymodule.js&#x27; in the same path as the page
        import { q } from &#x27;mymodule&#x27;;

        new q(); // -> &#x27;this is an es6 class!&#x27;
    </script>
</code></pre>
You can use it today with things like : <a href="https://github.com/ModuleLoader/es6-module-loader" rel="nofollow">https://github.com/ModuleLoader/es6-module-loader</a>
